## Summary

The inbound-media **writer** and the user-turn-transcript **reader** hold directly contradictory contracts for the parallel `Media*` arrays, so attachment content-types (and URLs) are assigned to the **wrong attachment** whenever an earlier attachment lacks a type/url.

**Writer** — `alignedStrings`, `src/channels/inbound-event/media.ts:35-42` (pads holes with `""` to *keep* index alignment):
```ts
function alignedStrings(values: Array<string | undefined>): string[] | undefined {
  if (!values.some(Boolean)) {
    return undefined;
  }
  // Preserve indexes across parallel Media* arrays so transcribed indexes and
  // media metadata continue to refer to the same attachment.
  return values.map((value) => value ?? "");
}
```

**Reader** — `normalizeOptionalTextArray`, `src/sessions/user-turn-transcript.ts:142-148`, called by `buildPersistedUserTurnMediaInputsFromFields` (`:176-178`) (drops the `""` holes, then indexes positionally):
```ts
function normalizeOptionalTextArray(
  values: readonly (string | null | undefined)[] | null | undefined,
): string[] {
  return (
    values?.map(normalizeOptionalText).filter((value): value is string => Boolean(value)) ?? []
  );
}
// :176-178
const paths = normalizeOptionalTextArray(fields.MediaPaths);
const urls = normalizeOptionalTextArray(fields.MediaUrls);
const types = normalizeOptionalTextArray(fields.MediaTypes);
```

Because one array gets compacted and another doesn't, index `i` no longer refers to the same attachment. Reached on every inbound media turn via `src/auto-reply/reply/get-reply-run.ts:1210` → `buildPersistedUserTurnMediaInputsFromFields(ctx)`.

## Impact

| Inbound (writer, index-aligned) | Persisted (after reader) | Correct |
|---|---|---|
| `a.bin` (no type), `b.png` (`image/png`) | `a.bin → image/png` ❌, `b.png → image/png` (right value, wrong reason) ❌ | `a.bin → undefined` (no derivable type), `b.png → image/png` |

A non-image attachment is mislabeled with a later attachment's MIME type; the real `image/png` is shifted off its true attachment (it lands on `b.png` only because compaction collapsed the array to a single element). The same failure hits `MediaUrls` when an earlier attachment has a path but no URL. **Severity: low–moderate** — it corrupts persisted transcript metadata (not message routing), and only on multi-attachment turns where an earlier attachment lacks a type/url (common for raw files/blobs). No crash, no message loss.

## Proposed fix

Stop compacting the parallel arrays in the reader — map per-index and let the `""` holes normalize to `undefined`, which the builder's existing per-index `??` lookups already treat as "absent":
```ts
function normalizeOptionalTextArray(
  values: readonly (string | null | undefined)[] | null | undefined,
): (string | undefined)[] {
  return values?.map(normalizeOptionalText) ?? [];
}
```
`buildPersistedUserTurnMediaInputsFromFields` is unchanged: it already derives `mediaCount` from `Math.max(paths.length, urls.length, …)` and reads each index with `types[index] ?? (index === 0 ? singleType : undefined)`, so an `undefined` hole falls through correctly and `mediaCount` becomes the true attachment count. The single-field fallbacks (`MediaType` at index 0) are unaffected.

**Sibling-contrast:** the writer (`alignedStrings`) and `MediaTranscribedIndexes` both go to explicit lengths specifically to keep index → attachment stable (the writer's comment: *"so transcribed indexes and media metadata continue to refer to the same attachment"*). The reader is the lone consumer that re-compacts, breaking the invariant the rest of the pipeline maintains.

**Provenance:** the writer's alignment-padding (`07f05e972e`) and the reader's compacting normalizer (`833520b13a`) were introduced in **separate refactors** and never reconciled.

## Reproduction (real exported reader, no mocks)

Input `{ MediaPaths: ["/media/a.bin","/media/b.png"], MediaTypes: ["","image/png"] }`.

Real output on **current main** (buggy):
```
OUT /media/a.bin => image/png      <-- WRONG (belongs to b.png)
OUT /media/b.png => image/png
```
Real output after the fix:
```
OUT /media/a.bin => undefined      <-- correct: no type borrowed from the next attachment
OUT /media/b.png => image/png
```

> Heads-up for triage: `src/sessions/user-turn-transcript.ts` is being actively refactored (a session-seam routing change plus several open PRs touch the file) — none touch `buildPersistedUserTurnMediaInputsFromFields`/`normalizeOptionalTextArray`, but the fix may want rebasing if that work lands first. I have a branch ready and am happy to open the PR.

